,You are crossing the boundaries of what SimpleNLG can do. It would be great if SimpleNLG could understand that ""5"" (or ""five"") bares numerical meaning and that ""delicious"" denotes quality, in which case the system would know how to order things. But reality is different: to SimpleNLG ""5"" and ""delicious"" are just strings, completely disjoint from any semantics they could carry.
